  "prompt": "Do some people without mental illnesses see therapists?",
  "response": "Yes, many people without diagnosed mental illnesses see therapists. Therapy can be beneficial for anyone looking to improve their mental health, gain insight into their behaviors and thoughts, work on personal development, or navigate life's challenges. People often seek therapy for reasons such as managing stress, improving relationships, dealing with grief or loss, enhancing self-esteem, or achieving personal goals. Therapy can be a proactive approach to maintaining mental well-being, not just a reactive measure for mental illness.",
